column1: Note: there are more sheets in this document
Each session is found on its own sheet below. There is a session for each time you have renewed these questions.

column5: What are my confidence level in my...: - Understand the benefits of object-oriented development
column6: What are my confidence level in my...:     - Learn the definition and characteristics of an object, including its ability to save state and perform operations.
column7: What are my confidence level in my...:     - Comprehend the principles of object-oriented development, such as information hiding, encapsulation, and message passing.
column8: What are my confidence level in my...:     - Understand the definition and structure of a class as a collection of objects with common traits and behaviors.
column9: What are my confidence level in my...:     - Recognize the importance of relationships between classes, including association, composition, and aggregation, in class diagrams.
column10: What are my confidence level in my...: I understand why function design is important
column11: What are my confidence level in my...: - I can give some features of good function design
column12: What are my confidence level in my...: - I can give a function a proper name
column13: What are my confidence level in my...: - I can criticise functions
column14: What are my confidence level in my...: - I can write a class to express what the data it contains
column15: What are my confidence level in my...: - I inderstand difference between composition and aggregation
column16: What are my confidence level in my...: - I understand the type of relation 'composition' is
column17: What are my confidence level in my...: - I understand the type of relation 'inheritance' is
column18: What are my confidence level in my...: Understand the concept of code smells and design smells.
column19: What are my confidence level in my...:     Gain an introductory understanding of modular programming
column20: What are my confidence level in my...:     Learn about common interfaces, protocols, and their role in modular programming.
column21: What are my confidence level in my...: Recognize and address tight coupling in code to improve modularity.
column22: What are my confidence level in my...: Iterative refactoring.
